rb laughlin benjamin franklin medal benjamin franklin medal for physics prof robert b laughlin department of physics stanford university stanford ca 94305 the benjamin franklin medal is an given annually by the franklin institute in a several categories ranging from pure science to engineering and entrepreneurship prof laughlin shared the 1998 franklin medal with dan tsui and horst stormer for the same work that won them the nobel prize later that year the franklin medal is approximately 1.5 inches across the award ceremony took place at the franklin institute auditorium in philadelphia in april 1998 it was an impressive hollywood style production complete with red carpets trumpets and an engaging audience bejeweled with diamonds a lovely reception and dinner followed
